Fundamental analysis 21/07/2020:
üî¥Asia-Pacific Region: The first Asian session this week took place in active sales in the stock markets, after the release of failed statistics on Japan. The country increased its trade deficit and reduced export volumes, significantly worse than analysts' expectations. Chinese indices rose strongly on the results of the People's Bank meeting. The regulator left the rate unchanged, but the published report showed an increase in investments from the United States, as well as an increase in foreign investments in the telecommunications and IT sectors.
üîµUS: US investors have greeted media reports of successful vaccine development at Oxford University with enthusiasm. The drug ChAdOx1 nCoV-19 produced antibodies and T cells in all volunteers participating in the trial.
üü†EU: The main event of the European session was the 4th day of the EU summit, instead of the planned two-day meetings. EU heads of state share a trillionth coronavirus budget. Markets grew thanks to the first compromise, the opposition from 4 countries agreed on a compromise level of grants - 390 billion euros. Now the Netherlands, Denmark, Sweden and Austria will have to be persuaded to withdraw their demands to deprive countries of aid that do not share common European values. Poland and Hungary are against it, as they will not be able to receive subsidies and cheap loans. The head of the European Council, Charles Michel, prepared a compromise version of the budget, with significantly reduced criteria for the conditions for observing common European values. The summit will last for the fifth day, which will be a new 20-year record for such summit meetings of EU leaders. The FTSE index fell into the outsiders of the session, after deciding to suspend the extradition agreement with Hong Kong. China is threatening the British economy with unfriendly gestures.

Fundamental analysis 24/07/2020:
üü†Asia-Pacific Region: Asian indices ended the session on Thursday in different directions, the Japanese stock market was closed, Australia won back the rally in gold, Hong Kong investors perceived the disagreement between the US and China as a positive factor. The two mainland exchanges of the PRC practically did not react to the diplomatic scandal, the Shenzhen Composite managed to close in plus, thanks to the Tesla report. Korea's KOSPI has suffered the most. The United States is gathering allies and can demand support from the country in the confrontation with China.
üîµUS: Higher-than-expected growth in unemployment benefits triggered sales in US stocks on Thursday. They intensified after Donald Trump's statement on the loss of interest in concluding the second part of the agreement with China. China was not against the continuation of the negotiations, despite the diplomatic scandal, apparently the US President no longer considers this incentive capable of adding points to him in the election race.
üü¢European investors sold shares for the second session in a row, despite the positive statistics of the economic recovery in Germany, the consumer price index came out above analysts' forecasts. By the evening, the EU negotiator Michel Barnier brought the negativity, reporting an ineffectual second round of Brexit negotiations. There is less and less time left to conclude an economic agreement, but the British representative David Frost once again stressed the country's unwillingness to extend the transition period. Perhaps the specter of a hard Brexit will spoil the end of the year for European investors, but now the UK has a strong negotiating position, which is reflected in the positive FTSE rate.

Hello dear Subs! As You may witnessed, there have been no signals for 10 days and I should say that it‚Äôs one of the worst time periods to trade right now in terms of my approach to the financial markets.

Followed by a sequence of unprofitable weeks, I decided to stop trading until the 11th of January, or probably even further, until the second half of January.

messages.text:

Asian markets fell on Tuesday, investors were belatedly winning back yesterday's slowdown in China's economy and current statistics. Traders were disappointed by the decrease in job vacancies in Japan, worse than the estimates of analysts and the results of the RBA meeting. The Central Bank of Australia kept the rate, leaving the forecasts of GDP and unemployment unchanged.

The fall in US indices on Tuesday was a technical correction for the strong growth at the beginning of the week. The focus of attention of Western investors was the statement of the party secretary of the People's Bank of China. Guo Shuqing has accused the world's central banks of inflating the bubble, calling for a review of soft financial policy. The threat of a possible rise in rates prevented traders from reacting to the speech of the US President. Joe Biden at a press conference promised to stockpile vaccines for the entire adult population of North America by May this year.

The draft of a new strategy for trade policy of the European Union, brought stock indexes to plus in the session on Tuesday. Brussels invited countries to rebuild their economies, primarily by supporting innovation, green technologies and small business. The EU will fight harder against external challenges, responding to them with a policy of sanctions coordinated with other developed countries, in particular the United States. This will help defend the interests of companies in foreign markets.

text: Asian indices rose on Wednesday on positive statistics and external background. The annual decline in Australia's GDP turned out to be less than forecasted, and the growth of the gross product in the IV quarter was higher than the preliminary estimates. The Chinese PMI in the services sector delighted traders by matching analysts' expectations.

The reason for the decline in US stock exchanges on Wednesday was the testimony of data on employment, compiled by analysts before the release of the NFP on Friday. Collected figures from business sources showed a decline in jobs. This negative was exacerbated by the release of the purchasing managers' index, worse than the preliminary estimates. Among the fundamental reasons that intensified the sale of shares, it is worth noting the speech of the head of the US Department of State Anthony Blinken. The White House is pushing forward a green energy agenda that promises lower revenues for the extractive industries. Markets have also incorporated rumors into the indices of the Fed's "Twist" operation, familiar to traders from 2011-2012. It consists of replacing short-term bonds on the department's balance sheet with long-term treasuries, which can lead to an increase in the dollar.

The FTSE index became the leader of trading on Wednesday, thanks to the new budget of the UK, which provides an additional 65 billion pounds for economic recovery. The rest of the stock indexes closed in positive territory on the background of the growth of PMI of the services sector in the Eurozone.

text: Asian markets were hit by a wave of sales on Thursday, the negative came from the American markets, where the indices fell under the pressure of the soaring yields of the American Treasuries. The US government debt market makes investors nervous, who are afraid of curtailing stimulus programs and tightening monetary policy of world central banks.

The head of the Federal Reserve again did not convince investors that the financial department will be able to continue its soft policy in the face of a sharp jump in inflation. Jerome Powell acknowledged the problem of rising Treasury yields, speaking at an online conference, but did not voice any measures to fight it. Yesterday's unemployment benefits were below analysts' forecasts, pushing short-term bond yields to new highs, sending stock indices to lows for the week. Additional pressure on the stock market was exerted by oil, which soared by 5% after OPEC decided not to increase production. Growing energy prices stimulate price growth and further accelerate inflation.

European markets on Thursday became an island of stability amid strong selloffs in stock exchange assets in Asia and the United States. Analysts show that the EU countries have not yet touched the problem of accelerating inflation, lockdowns have reduced retail sales and consumer demand, preventing price increases. On the other hand, the EU authorities managed to reduce unemployment amid the pandemic, which was positively assessed by investors. In 19 EU countries, it was 8.1% in January, the lowest value since June 2020.

Asian markets ended Friday lower, investors doubt the adequacy of the perception of the economic situation by the US and Chinese governments. Jerome Powell's speech proved that the Fed does not want to notice the spiral of inflation, despite the rise in consumer prices and a sharp recovery in the labor market.  China, on the other hand, is ignoring the slowdown in economic performance.  Speaking at the session of representatives of the National Assembly, Premier of the State Council of the People's Republic of China Li Keqiang declared the goal of 6% GDP growth

The decline in unemployment and strong growth in new jobs (outside of agriculture) led to active buying of shares on the US stock markets.  Investors also pledged for a bailout package by the Senate, which did endorse a $ 1.9 trillion stimulus this Sunday.  Now the floor is for the House of Representatives, which must vote again due to the changes introduced by the senators.

European investors were frightened by the new record yield of short-term US Treasuries, which exceeded the level of 1.6%.  The rate attracts equity investors with a risk-free profit opportunity and increases the pressure on the stock market due to the depreciation of the euro.  The combination of these factors resulted in a negative close of Friday‚Äôs trading session.

text: The growth of inflation in the PRC, higher than the forecasts of experts, led to sales in the Asian markets, but raised the exchange rates of mainland China. They played back an increase in lending, which alarmed investors due to the high probability of a credit bubble that could lead to a new global economic crisis.

The adoption of the stimulus package by the House of Representatives on Wednesday became the main stimulus for the growth of US indices. Additional drivers for the purchase of shares were: a decrease in the annual inflation rate and an increase in the federal budget deficit, below analysts' forecasts. The statistics indicate the correctness of the assertions of the head of the Federal Reserve, Jerome Powell, that the spiral of inflation does not threaten the US economy yet.

Trading on European markets was in line with world news due to the lack of its own statistics on Wednesday. Traders recovered positively from rising inflation in China and falling Treasury yields in the United States. Purchases of shares were driven by the decrease in pressure on the euro from the dollar for the second session in a row.

text: Asian markets were dominated by purchases on Friday, investors returned capital to equities from bonds and other defensive instruments, counting on a wave of growth in international indices. The Hong Kong market fell out of the general trend, due to the adoption of a new law, adjusting the electoral system in the autonomy in order to fight the opposition.

US Treasury Secretary Janet Yellen said on Friday that American citizens will begin to receive checks for $1.4 thousand. This is the second package of aid from the state, almost all the funds of the first package in the amount of $1,000 were invested in shares. This factor was the reason for the growth of the indices in the last session of the week. Buyers bypassed tech stocks, which are considered overbought due to strong takeoffs during the 2020 economic crisis.

The results of the European Friday session were determined by statistics. The British stock index rose on data from January GDP, which exceeded preliminary estimates of experts, the purchase of European shares ensured the rise of industrial production in the EU. The German DAX index fell out of the general trend. Investors were counting on the growth of inflation, the dynamics of which decreased in February, but coincided with analysts' estimates.

American markets rallied in the absence of economic news, thanks to the US President's European voyage. Joe Biden attended the summit in Brussels yesterday and held a number of bilateral meetings. Ahead is a summit with the EU, where the United States will reset its relations with Europe, which did not develop with Trump.

The first working day led to a multidirectional closure of European indices. The positive sentiment of traders was caused by the growth of industrial production in the Eurozone and the cost of a barrel. Oil has set a price record after statements by the spokesman for the Iranian Foreign Ministry Said Khatibzad about the delay in lifting the embargo.

Bitcoin climbed above $ 40,000 on news of the expansion of crypto instruments at Goldman Sachs. The financial conglomerate will open up access to Ethereum futures and options for clients, in the wake of the growing popularity of this cryptocurrency. 

Investors seem to disagree, judging by the record withdrawals from funds focused on Ethereum. On the contrary,the withdrawal of Bitcoin funds has significantly decreased.

text: The released RBA Protocol led to an increase in the Australian index, after the statements of the Central Bank to extend the soft monetary policy until 2021. All exchanges, except China, showed a positive attitude. The reason for the fall of the PRC indices was the unequivocal position of the G7 countries and NATO on condemning the domestic and foreign policies of this state.

American investors were disappointed with politics and statistics on Tuesday. The fall in the indices is associated with the release of retail sales, below the expectations of experts and the rise in producer prices, above preliminary estimates, which indicates a potential increase in future inflation. The European voyage of the US President did not bring any breakthroughs. Participation in the G7 summits and Biden's bilateral meetings have so far ended with common phrases and framework agreements.

Tuesday's trading session ended with growth for European exchanges, thanks to the release of inflation data in large EU economies in line with analysts' expectations. Consumer prices in France were below their expectations, the UK posted employment below preliminary estimates. Inflation and the labor market are indicators that determine the monetary policy of the ECB and the Bank of England, the figures of which give hope to investors for the extension of QE stimulus by the central banks.

The Bitcoin rate slightly dipped 0.57% on Tuesday after the breakthrough of quotations into the $4,000 zone. The total cryptocurrency capitalization lost 0.71%. The speculators' attention is focused on actively adding new types of digital currencies to the Coinbase list.

This is one of the features of the crypto market, the price of an altcoin or token skyrockets when it is listed on a major exchange.

text: Asian markets were expected to fall on Thursday's trading session. Traders were not expecting a hawkish sentiment in the Fed's announcements, which saw the number of votes in favor of rate hikes in 2022 and 2023 doubled in half. Investors ignored the decline in unemployment in Australia to a record 5.1%, but actively bought shares of Chinese companies. The Chinese and Hong Kong markets rose on the decision of the authorities to sell significant volumes of metals from the state reserve at reduced prices. The raw materials will be sent to local enterprises, which will be a measure of support for the business. An additional impetus for growth was the statement by the US National Security Adviser Jake Sullivan about the preparations for a meeting between Joe Biden and Chinese leader Xi Jinping.

American markets continued their decline on Thursday, which began at the end of the Fed meeting. The mood of traders was worsened by the released figures of unemployment benefits, which rose above analysts' forecasts.

The statistics of growth in car sales and inflation in the Eurozone, above analysts' forecasts, showed investors that the economy is recovering at an accelerated pace. Economic indicators provided a positive close for stock indices on Thursday.  The British Stock Exchange was among the outsiders, investors are preparing for negative statistics, which are released today - a drop in retail sales amid problems with Brexit.

text: A strong drop in US indices on Friday negatively affected the first trading week in Asia. The Nikkei index became the leader of the sale of shares, investors consider the ongoing Summer Olympics a problem for Japan, where 3.2% of the population received two doses of the vaccine. The influx of tourists and athletes could lead to a new wave of Covid-19.  Stock indices in mainland China closed in positive territory, thanks to the preservation of the parameters of monetary policy by the People's Bank.

Record low yields in short-term treasuries showed that investors returned to actively buying stocks that had fallen in price. Obviously, traders are betting that the highest point of inflation this year has been passed.

European investors finished the first trading session of the week in active buying of shares. Stock indices rose after the speech of Ursula von der Leyen. The President of the European Commission announced that an agreement had been reached with the United States to discuss ways to lift sanctions on the export of steel and aluminum.

The People's Bank of China caused the Bitcoin price to collapse to the lows of the year. The Financial Regulator held a meeting with representatives of the two largest banks and the Alipay payment system, where he demanded to stop servicing accounts related to cryptocurrency.  In practice, this means that individuals and companies caught in the exchange of digital currencies will be included in the unspoken "black list" of the Chinese banking system, forever losing the opportunity to work with non-cash in China.  The decision of the authorities means financial death for OTC crypto exchange services and mining farms, which led to a decrease in Bitcoin to $31.000.

text: Strong gains in US indices on Monday caused buying activity in Asian markets on Tuesday. All platforms, without exception, have grown, betting on the positive speech of the head of the FRS before the US Congress.

The US stock exchanges ended the day in a positive zone, investors believed the speech of the head of the Fed in the US Congress about the temporality of inflation growth. Investors do not believe in a favorable outcome of the negotiations between Iran and the United States, despite the positive statements on this occasion by Ibrahim Raisi. The new president of the Islamic Republic assumes that the embargo will be lifted from the country at the next stages of the meetings. According to rumors, the United States does not plan to lift the restrictions, it is at best about freezing for 90 or 180 days.

The Bitcoin rate continues to update the lows of the year, having dropped to $28,800 in yesterday's trading, losing 5.16%. The total cryptocurrency capitalization fell by a less dramatic 0.71% to $1.322 trillion, with a 15% increase in trading volumes.

Despite the collapse of digital currencies, large companies have not diminished interest in this industry. Payment services PayPal and Visa, invested $300 million in the Blockchain Capital fund, which invests venture capital in tokens and shares of startups focused on blockchain technologies and the development of new types of altcoins.

text: US President Joe Biden's speech coincided with the opening of Asian markets on Friday. The announcement of an agreement with the US Congress on spending on infrastructure in the amount of $1 trillion, provided a positive mood on all Asia-Pacific exchanges, which closed in positive area at the end of the day.

US indices managed to close Friday at record highs, thanks to lower consumer spending dynamics. Investors took the negative statistics positively, they prove the Fed's assumption about the reduction of the current exorbitant inflation rate by the end of the year. Problems arose only in the sector of shares of IT companies. Traders consider them to be overbought due to strong gains at the end of 2020.

Friday's European session was influenced by local news. The DAX index rose after the release of the German consumer climate index, better than analysts' forecasts. The speech of the head of the Bank of England, filled with promises to maintain a soft monetary policy, raised the FTSE100 rate. The French CAC40 ended the day in the negative area. Investors withdrew from stocks ahead of the second round of regional elections, fearing the failure of the party of incumbent President Macron.

There has been a reversal in the cryptocurrency market, with the total value of digital currencies growing by 5.85% on Sunday. Bitcoin overtook the overall trend, adding 7.6%, traders ignore the negative from the mining industry. 

The computing power of the BTC miners dropped to a new low this year, and the mining of blocks at the input was twice as slow as standard values. The fall in demand for ASIC miners, due to the ban on this industry in China, is "drowning" the business of the largest hardware manufacturer Bitmain. The company refused to order 5 nm chips for $300 million.

The banning of Binance in Canada, the UK and Japan is another worrying piece of news. The company ranks first in the world in terms of trading volume and its problems can undermine the credibility of centralized exchanges.

Asian markets finished trading on Monday with minor changes, despite the late opening of the session in Hong Kong and the decline in the dynamics of profits of the PRC industrial enterprises. The indicator increased 36.4% in May, below the April growth data of 57%.

American indices continued their gains on Monday, except for the DJ, which fell on forecasts of a decrease in quarterly profits of its member companies. The S&P500 and NASDAQ records are associated with the Fed's decision to remove restrictions on the payment of dividends and buyback operations imposed by the regulator during the pandemic.

European markets fell after reports from the UK about the maximum daily increase in coronavirus cases. Despite active vaccinations in the country, 22,686 people were hospitalized with Covid-19 on Monday. Thus, the forecasts of the WHO researcher Sumya Swaminatan, who warned of a new wave of coronavirus in the world, provoked by the spread of the more infectious Delta mutation, are justified.

Bitcoin on Monday tested the level of $34,900, but at the end of the day it lost all growth, closing the session with a minus of 0.39%. The total cryptocurrency capitalization grew slightly by 1.25% or $1.438 billion.

The news about Morgan Stanley's contribution to the Grayscale Bitcoin Trust gave the market a positive mood. The world's largest investment bank has acquired 28,200 shares backed by Bitcoin, according to a US SEC report.

Soon there will be more such news, the American Regulator discloses information about large positions in securities at the end of each quarter. Bitcoin will grow if "new faces" appear in the reporting.

text: Let's start with fundamental analysis for this week:

Celebrating the 100th anniversary of the Chinese Communist Party left a negative aftermath on Asian stock markets on Friday. Threats in the speech of Secretary General Xi Jinping sent negative shares of the exchanges of China, Hong Kong and Korea. High energy prices supported the growth of the Australian S&P / ASX200. Japan's Nikkei 225 rallied on the gains of large enterprises, indicated by the Tankan indicators a day earlier.

Asian markets did not show a uniform performance on Monday. The Nikkei and Hong Kong's Hang Seng fell on fears of an increase in the coronavirus, as well as negative statistics from China, where the published PMI was below analysts' forecasts. On the contrary, the mainland exchanges of the PRC perceived the drop in business activity as a guarantee of the continuation of the soft policy of the People's Bank. In Australia, the stock index also showed growth along with retail sales, which came out above preliminary estimates.

Asian markets did not show a uniform performance on Tuesday. Chinese exchanges and Hong Kong fell on the results of trilateral negotiations between the heads of China, France and Germany. The online meeting did not solve the problems of European business in China. European countries have not abandoned plans for joint coordination of sanctions against China. The Australian market dropped due to monetary tightening. The RBA will cut QE volumes, but will leave the rate unchanged. The rest of the Asian exchanges rose in anticipation of a positive gap at the US open.

The dynamics of the indices of the American stock exchanges on Friday depended on the level of employment in the United States, which rose above forecasts. Along with it, analysts' estimates overtook the trade deficit and industrial orders of enterprises, which determined the new highs of the stock market.
American markets were closed on Monday.

ISM indices hit the US stock market, showing worse-than-expected declines in business activity, amid high inflationary expectations. At the end of the session, purchases returned to the market, after information appeared about an agreement between the OPEC countries to increase the oil production quota.

Eurozone investors chose a cautious tactic on the last day of trading, closing positions near zero. Only the German market turned out to be positive, where investors bought shares against news about the official visit of the German Chancellor to the UK.

European indices rose slightly on Monday, low trading activity is explained by closed American markets. The growth leader was the British FTSE100, which responded to the cancellation of all coronavirus restrictions in the country from July 19, announced by Prime Minister Boris Johnson. The rest of the European markets ended the day in positive territory thanks to online trilateral talks between the heads of France, Germany and China.

Stock indexes in Europe fell under pressure without the performance of the OPEC meeting and statistics. The countries of the oil cartel could not agree on the distribution of quotas because of the disagreement with the UAE, which led first to an increase in prices, and then to its panic fall. The collapse of the OPEC deal could lead to an uncontrolled filling of the market with oil. A sharp decline in the volume of industrial orders from German enterprises added negative news. Analysts expected this indicator to rise.

Bitcoin managed to hold the $34,000 level despite yesterday's wave of negative news. The cryptocurrency market as a whole rose on Tuesday, adding +1.05% to capitalization.

International pressure on the largest exchange Binance forced the company to abandon SEPA transfers. Elon Musk's idea to invest part of Tesla's assets in BTC turned into a loss of $100 million, as the financial report of the second quarter will show.

China continues to target cryptocurrency-related companies by blocking the website, account and registration of one of the local brokers.

Among the positive news, it is worth noting the arrival on the cryptocurrency market of the hedge fund Marshall Wace, its turnover is $155 million.

text: The positive closure of Asian indices on Tuesday was provided by the data of import/export and trade balance of China. The indicators significantly exceeded the preliminary estimates of analysts. The PRC increased the volume of supplies and purchases with all developed countries except Australia, which was reflected in the decline in S&P/ASX 200.

Asian markets fell on Wednesday following the US stock exchanges, which won back the negative of record inflation yesterday. The released statistics of Japan increased the pressure on the indices by the fall of the country's industrial production in May by 6.5% against the forecast of a decline of 5.9%. Shares in Korean companies fell marginally, thanks to a decline in unemployment to 3.7%. Australian S&P/ASX 200 showed resilience to the negative amid high oil prices.

Record inflation in the United States became the main topic of the day, hitting the stock and foreign exchange markets. The dollar index strengthened against all currencies, and shares fell in price after the release of consumer inflation of 5.4%. According to the Fed's forecasts, this figure should have dropped below 5%. Now the financial regulator will be forced to reduce the QE program.

The speech of the head of the Fed in Congress and the approval by the Democrats of budget expenditures for $3.5 trillion, which will go to medicine and the fight against poverty, brought the indices to plus, except for the NASDAQ. Jerome Powell managed to positively influence the markets, inform the Congressmen about the need for further market support due to weak employment and high unemployment.

European markets finished trading near zero, undecided on the trend. Among the important news of the past auction, it is worth noting the joint Council of Europe with the US Treasury Secretary Janet Yellen, who obtained a promise from the EU to postpone the condemnation of the digital tax on US IT companies until the implementation of the minimum international corporate tax rate.

European investors left the indices at zero levels on Wednesday, the negative unwinding of the inflation spiral blocked the positive of the current news. The EU has approved 16 plans for economic recovery after the pandemic, countries will receive funds from the fund for 750 billion euros. Vice President of the European Commission Franz Timmermans presented for discussion a large-scale plan to combat climate change with a set of benefits and financial preferences for companies.

text: Asian markets in the last session of the week did not show uni dynamics. Chinese indices fell on the next round of tensions between the United States and China. China has imposed sanctions against a number of US officials who will not go unanswered. The rest of the markets rose following a three-day rally in US indices. The Japan Stock Exchange is closed for the Tokyo Summer Olympics.

The main attention of investors at the session on Wednesday was attracted by the collapse of the Chinese market, which occurred due to the fault of the new regulatory initiatives of the PRC. Shares of educational companies have depreciated by 60-70% after the ban on foreign capital participation in them, placement on foreign stock exchanges.  The problems were added by an unsuccessful attempt to find a compromise between the United States and China during a visit to the China by the Deputy Secretary of State of the White House. Foreign investors rushed to sell off the national debt, the yuan collapsed.
Positive corporate reporting and higher than analysts' forecasts PMI, became the reason for new all-time highs in US indices on Friday.

American investors again ignored the negative statistics signals. The demand for durable goods turned out to be below the forecasts of experts. However, preliminary estimates on the consumer confidence index and oil reserves were exceeded, where a deficit has emerged, indicating a rapid economic recovery.  The White House's decision to mandate vaccinations for federal employees, announced by President Joe Biden in a speech to intelligence officials, was also well received by investors. At the end of the session, the growth impetus was given by the reports of IT companies that increased their quarterly revenue: Apple (+ 36%), Microsoft (+ 18%), Google (+ 62%).

The positive dynamics of the European stock indices on Friday was determined by the ECB meeting the day before and the statistics released at the end of the week. The European Central Bank left the rate unchanged, the growth of which will not be affected by the inflation rate exceeding 2%, and also guaranteed the current QE volumes until the end of 2022.
The negative fall in Chinese markets led to sales on European exchanges, which were traded on Tuesday without the release of their own news.

Bitcoin quotes at the beginning of the week tested the $40,000 mark, having increased by 25% per day. The reason for the growth was information about Amazon's decision to support the sale of goods for cryptocurrencies. 
The IT company denied these rumors, provoking a rebound in the course. Traders also drew attention to information about the start of an investigation in the United States against Tether and new negativity around the largest crypto exchange Binance. The site reduced its leverage and refused to trade derivatives in AUD, GBP and EUR. 
Information about the launch of an ETF fund by Goldman Sachs, which is focused on DeFi tokens, can support the further growth of the cryptocurrency rate today.

Unexpected growth of PMI in Germany and business sentiment in the industrial sector of the Eurozone led to active purchases of shares on European exchanges. Experts predicted a slowdown in the EU economy.

text: The price of energy, on the way to the breakthrough of psychological price levels, became the reason for the sale of shares on the APR exchange. The People's Bank of China managed to stimulate the purchase of securities on the stock exchanges of the country, thanks to the injection of another portion of liquidity of $ 15.5 billion.

American and global investors are actively withdrawing capital from stocks into American Treasuries. As a result, 10-year bonds have renewed their six-month record, with the yield on 5 and 30-year bonds exceeding 1% and 2%.  Paradoxically, the high demand for US debt securities is taking place against the backdrop of the specter of default. According to US Treasury Secretary Janette Yellen, the Treasury on October 18 will run out of money to service the national debt.

Gas at $1000 and oil at $80 per barrel definitely accelerate future inflation in the Eurozone, which previously hit the 3% barrier. Investors on Tuesday showed by selling shares on European stock exchanges that they do not believe in the possibility of keeping the ECB's soft monetary policy rate.
